1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,480
AI conversations quickly become a second workspace. After months of use,

2
00:00:05,480 --> 00:00:10,961
active projects are mixed with old versions, repeated decisions, forgotten

3
00:00:10,961 --> 00:00:16,441
tasks, and unrelated questions. ChatGPT Project Organizer turns exported

4
00:00:16,441 --> 00:00:21,921
conversations into structured, evidence-backed, and reversible projects.

5
00:00:21,921 --> 00:00:27,807
The workflow starts by importing JSON, CSV, or TXT. Source files are copied

6
00:00:27,807 --> 00:00:33,693
into protected storage, hashed, normalized, and never edited. The included

7
00:00:33,693 --> 00:00:39,579
anonymized demo contains thirty-three conversations and fifty-one messages.

8
00:00:39,579 --> 00:00:44,631
Before using a language model, deterministic rules identify objective signals:

9
00:00:44,631 --> 00:00:49,684
exact and partial duplicates, version precedence, approved or rejected decisions,

10
00:00:49,684 --> 00:00:54,737
pending tasks, and explicit project states. Every finding keeps the exact

11
00:00:54,737 --> 00:00:59,790
conversation evidence that supports it.

12
00:00:59,790 --> 00:01:05,624
GPT-5.6 then reconstructs semantic project context through the OpenAI Responses

13
00:01:05,624 --> 00:01:11,459
API and a strict Pydantic Structured Output. It identifies seven projects,

14
00:01:11,459 --> 00:01:17,293
current and discarded versions, decisions, tasks, blockers, memberships,

15
00:01:17,293 --> 00:01:23,128
and ambiguous cases. The reproducible demo is clearly labelled as precomputed.

16
00:01:23,128 --> 00:01:28,962
Live mode uses GPT-5.6 when an API key is configured.

17
00:01:28,962 --> 00:01:33,312
The application generates one global proposal instead of asking the user

18
00:01:33,312 --> 00:01:37,662
to organize every chat. Sixteen safe operations can be approved as a batch.

19
00:01:37,662 --> 00:01:42,011
Only four exceptions require correction or rejection, so human attention

20
00:01:42,011 --> 00:01:46,361
is focused where it matters.

21
00:01:46,361 --> 00:01:50,423
A mandatory before-and-after preview shows exactly what will change. Applying

22
00:01:50,423 --> 00:01:54,485
the proposal updates only a simulated derived workspace. The original conversations

23
00:01:54,485 --> 00:01:58,547
remain untouched, and every authorized operation is written to an ordered

24
00:01:58,547 --> 00:02:02,609
audit history.

25
00:02:02,609 --> 00:02:07,259
Undo restores the exact previous workspace hash while preserving audit history.

26
00:02:07,259 --> 00:02:11,909
Codex accelerated the architecture, React and FastAPI implementation, tests,

27
00:02:11,909 --> 00:02:16,560
debugging, release validation, and documentation. Human decisions defined

28
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:21,210
immutable originals, evidence precedence, approval gates, and the reversible

29
00:02:21,210 --> 00:02:25,860
workflow.

30
00:02:25,860 --> 00:02:30,668
The result is a working prototype where AI performs the heavy analysis without

31
00:02:30,668 --> 00:02:35,476
removing user control. It organizes knowledge, explains its decisions, protects

32
00:02:35,476 --> 00:02:40,284
the source, and makes every operation reversible.
